REVENUE. COST OF REVENUE INCREASED $700 MILLION OR 82%, PRIMARILY DRIVEN BY INCREASED ONLINE TRAFFIC ACQUISITION, DATA CENTER AND EQUIPMENT, AND HEADCOUNT-RELATED COSTS. RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT EXPENSES INCREASED $153 MILLION OR 17%, PRIMARILY DUE

TO INCREASED HEADCOUNT-RELATED EXPENSES.

